description: Where `.mdc` rules live, frontmatter, scope, quality bar
globs: "**/.cursor/rules/ai-rules/**/*.mdc"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Authoring `.mdc` rules

Path: `.cursor/rules/ai-rules/<subfolder>/<kebab-name>.mdc`. Short playbooks.

- **Name**: kebab-case; verb-first when natural. **`description`**: unique, picker-ready.
- **Frontmatter**: `description` (string); optional `globs` (path filter); `alwaysApply`—`true` only if worth every chat’s tokens.
- **Body**: one `#` title; bullets > prose; ❌/✅ snippets only if easy to misread; **~50 lines** max per file; split topics.
- **Quality**: actionable; real examples; no dupes (link); never commit secrets in rules.
- **Maintenance**: refresh examples when layout/APIs change; fix `mdc:` links on rename.

Checklist: valid path; parsable YAML; intentional scope; no duplicate guidance.
